attributeList.attribute: Transcriptional repressor with a role in determining the three cell types of Saccharomyces cerevisiae: the a and alpha haploid cells and the a/alpha diploid cell type. Binds to a 30- or 31-base-pair (bp) a-specific operator DNA, which contains the pseudosymmetric MCM1 16-bp P-box-binding site flanked on either side by alpha2-binding sites, to repress transcription of a-specific genes.

alpha2 uses a short eight-amino-acid module in the linker region to bind MCM1 via parallel beta-strands. This recognition strand is tethered to the alpha2 homeodomain by a segment of unusual conformational flexibility. Additional contacts are also made between the MATalpha2 homeodomain and MCM1.
